Yes, this is not a Saraswati mantra, but Hayagreeva mantra. Hayagreeva is a horse-headed form of Vishnu who gives higher learning.
 
When Vijay was doing aksharabhyasam to his daughter, I had suggested making offerings to five deities representing five aspects of learning corresponding to five elements - Ganapathi, Saraswati, Medha Devi (deity of intelligence), Medha Dakshinamurthy (teacher form of Shiva) and Hayagreeva. While there are various mantras for each (e.g. Medha sooktam for Medha Devi), the following are simple naama mantras.
 
